==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Plenary
<hw>Ple"na*ry</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[LL.
<ets>plenarius</ets>, fr. L. <ets>plenus</ets> full. See
<er>Plenty</er>.]</ety> <def>Full; entire; complete; absolute; <as>as, a
<ex>plenary</ex> license; <ex>plenary</ex> authority.</as></def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>A treatise on a subject should be <qex>plenary</qex> or full.</q>
<rj><qau>I. Watts.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Plenary indulgence</b></col> <fld>(R. C. Ch.)</fld>,
<cd>an entire remission of temporal punishment due to, or canonical
penance for, all sins.</cd> -- <col><b>Plenary inspiration</b></col>.
<fld>(Theol.)</fld> <cd>See under <er>Inspiration</er>.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Plenary</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Plenary
<hw>Ple"na*ry</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Law)</fld> <def>Decisive
procedure.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Plene</ent>⟦br⟧
